    "\n",
    "In this section, you will need to read the CSV files into DataFrames and perform any necessary data cleaning steps. After cleaning, combine all DataFrames into a single DataFrame.\n",
    "\n",
    "Files:\n",
    "\n",
    "* `whale_returns.csv`: Contains returns of some famous \"whale\" investors' portfolios.\n",

    "# Box plot to visually show risk\n",

    "combined_df.boxplot(figsize=(20,10));\n",
    "combined_df.mean().sort_values()"

We can see that TIGER GLOBAL MANAGEMENT LLC and BERKSHIRE HATHAWAY INC show their data is more expreded out than the other portfolios, is more volatil. Higher volatility bigger the risk. The Portfolio Algo_1, also shows high volatility."

    "print(f\"Algo_1_beta = {Algo_1_beta}\")"

    "#### I choose Portfolio Algo_1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,

   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "# Calculate 30-day rolling covariance of Algo 1 vs. S&P 500 and plot the data\n",
    "rolling_covariance_60 = combined_df['Algo_1'].rolling(window=60).cov(combined_df['S&P500'])\n",
    "rolling_covariance_60.plot(figsize=(20, 10), title='Rolling 60-Day Covariance of Algo 1 Returns vs. S&P 500 Returns');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate 30-day rolling variance of Algo 1 vs. S&P 500 and plot the data\n",
    "rolling_variance_60 = combined_df['S&P500'].rolling(window=60).var()\n",
    "rolling_variance_60.plot(figsize=(20, 10), title='Rolling 60-Day Variance of S&P 500 Returns');"
   ]

   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **Rolling Statistics Challenge: Exponentially Weighted Average**\n",
    "\n",
    "An alternative way to calculate a rolling window is to take the exponentially weighted moving average. This is like a moving window average, but it assigns greater importance to more recent observations. Try calculating the [`ewm`](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.ewm.html) with a 21-day half-life."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Use `ewm` to calculate the rolling window\n",
    "# https://www.statology.org/exponential-moving-average-pandas/\n",
    "\n",
    "combined_df.ewm(halflife=21).std().plot(figsize=(20,10), title='Rolling EWM, 21 days window, Half_life');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### This Rolling EWN Plot also corraborate the high volatility for TGM_LLC and BH__Inc and the lowest volatility for P_&_Co_Inc"
   ]

    "1. Choose 3-5 custom stocks with at last 1 year's worth of historic prices and create a DataFrame of the closing prices and dates for each stock.\n",
    "2. Calculate the weighted returns for the portfolio assuming an equal number of shares for each stock\n",
    "3. Join your portfolio returns to the DataFrame that contains all of the portfolio returns\n",
    "4. Re-run the performance and risk analysis with your portfolio to see how it compares to the others\n",

    "## **Calculate the weighted returns for the portfolio assuming an equal number of shares for each stock**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Date\n",
       "2018-05-14   -0.011152\n",
       "2018-05-15   -0.016677\n",
       "2018-05-16    0.003700\n",
       "2018-05-17    0.002589\n",
       "2018-05-18   -0.001557\n",
       "dtype: float64"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 56,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Set weights\n",
    "weights = [1/3, 1/3, 1/3]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate portfolio return\n",
    "portfolio_returns = daily_per_returns.dot(weights)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display sample data\n",
    "\n",
    " \n",
    "portfolio_returns.head()\n"
   ]

    "### **Calculate and Plot Rolling 60-day Beta for Your Portfolio compared to the S&P 500**"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 68,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.00010723654410358122"
      ]
     },

     "metadata": {},

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate and plot Beta\n",
    "Pport_covariance = portfolio_returns.cov(sp500_dayret['SP500'])\n",
    "Pport_covariance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "6.579270583158746e-05"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 69,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Joined_variance = sp500_dayret['SP500'].var()\n",
    "Joined_variance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 70,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "1.6299153948475598"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 70,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate beta of all daily returns of AMZN\n",
    "AMZN_beta = Pport_covariance / Joined_variance\n",
    "AMZN_beta"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 71,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate 60-day rolling covariance of AMZN vs. S&P 500 and plot the data\n",
    "J_rolling_covariance = portfolio_returns.rolling(window=60).cov(sp500_dayret['SP500'])\n",

    "### **How does your portfolio do?**\n",

    "#### Answer: My portfolio (AMZN, TSLA, KO) did not outperform the Algorithmic Strategies, but it has a high volatility and good Sharpe Ratio, making it a good investment due its good  risk/reward results (cumulate return was higher tha S&P 500)"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* In the Cumulative Return Plot we can see portfolios Algo_1 and BH_Inc have cumulative returns bigger than S&P 500, being Algo_1 the one with the Highest cumulative return over all, otherwise, P_G_Co_Inc was the portfolio with the lowest cumulative return over all..\n",
    "\n",
    "* In the Box Plot we could visualized the distribution of the data and conclude that TIGER GLOBAL MANAGEMENT LLC and BERKSHIRE HATHAWAY INC data are more expreded out or present more volatility. Higher volatility bigger the risk. The Portfolio Algo_1 also shows high volatility.\n",
    "\n",
    "* As TIGER GLOBAL MANAGEMENT LLC and BERKSHIRE HATHAWAY INC has showed the highest dispersion of a dataset they have the higher the standard deviation. Otherwise, P_&_Co_Inc shows the lowest STD.\n",
    "\n",
    "* The Correlation PLOT showed that the portfolio that mimic the S&P 500 behavior is __Algo_2, followed by SFM_LLC.\n",
    "\n",
    "* In the Rolling 60-Day Beta of Algo 1' vs S&P 500 we can see how disperse are Algo_1 data from S&P500 data. Algo_1 has a high volatility and does not follow the Market(S&P 500) \n",
    "\n",
    "* The Rolling EWN Plot also corroborate the high volatility for TGM_LLC and BH__Inc and the lowest volatility for P_&_C.\n",
    "\n",
    "* The Algorithmic Strategies (Algo_1 and Algo_2) outperform both, The market (S&P500) and The Whales Portfolios. The Algorithmic Strategies present a High Volatility and high accumulative return. It does not behave like the market, It represents the best strategy thanks to Portfolio Algo_1 who has the best performance in terms of volatility and accumulated return.\n",
    "\n",
